unless they want something from you.

31:44.320 --> 31:46.905
What we had, what we discovered,

31:46.906 --> 31:48.532
the work, at least...

31:50.159 --> 31:53.287
was special, and it was right.

31:54.371 --> 31:57.041
You are more than this case, Fitz,

31:59.460 --> 32:00.878
even if you don't believe it,

32:02.546 --> 32:04.256
even if they never give you credit for it.

32:05.549 --> 32:07.343
That has to mean something, right?

32:09.887 --> 32:10.888
What was that about credit?

32:12.681 --> 32:15.642
Credit--that is the way back in.
Ted wants to be famous.

32:15.643 --> 32:18.061
He wants everyone to know
how smart he is.

32:18.062 --> 32:20.105
The only way he's gonna get
the credit is to plead guilty.

32:22.149 --> 32:24.567
You bet the farm once before
that he'd need a trophy.

32:24.568 --> 32:26.235
- This is different.
- Look how that turned out.

32:26.236 --> 32:27.904
This is different.
You know that.

32:27.905 --> 32:29.530
You can convince me all night,

32:29.531 --> 32:31.241
but there's no way
Cole will let you in there.

32:34.787 --> 32:35.621
I'll go on my own.

32:36.538 --> 32:38.207
Make the call. I'll go tonight.

32:39.083 --> 32:41.251
It'll be off the record,
just me and Ted, face-to-face.

32:41.543 --> 32:43.628
I'll make--
I'll make it right.

32:43.629 --> 32:45.005
You make the call.

32:46.548 --> 32:48.008
Make the call.

33:02.356 --> 33:03.273
I'm off the case.

33:04.608 --> 33:05.651
I'm going home.

33:06.694 --> 33:09.154
I thought it best
if you heard it from me.

33:11.073 --> 33:13.367
There's one thing I would like
to ask you before I leave.

33:21.417 --> 33:23.961
Did you do all this because you wanted
to make a difference in the world,

33:24.128 --> 33:25.212
to change things?

33:26.088 --> 33:27.548
That's what I admired about you.

33:29.216 --> 33:30.801
You know, I admired you so much,

33:31.176 --> 33:34.471
I gave up everything
to live like you--

33:35.305 --> 33:37.599
alone in the woods,
manifesto under my bed.

33:39.268 --> 33:40.436
Is that true?

33:44.148 --> 33:45.649
When you asked for me,
I came, right?

33:47.151 --> 33:48.527
Yeah, you did, didn't you?

33:49.528 --> 33:51.864
Not many men whose ideas
can change the world.

33:53.490 --> 33:54.908
Now you're gonna throw it all away.

33:56.535 --> 33:58.203
I'm not throwing anything away.

33:59.705 --> 34:01.706
I'm beating the system at its own game.

34:01.707 --> 34:02.790
That's the whole point.

34:02.791 --> 34:05.668
Well, getting the search warrant
tossed out is beating the system.

34:05.669 --> 34:07.171
But what about after?

34:08.464 --> 34:10.006
Oh, you mean after.

34:10.007 --> 34:13.302
Well, I--I walk away a free man,

34:14.178 --> 34:18.766
vindicated as the victim of your sloppy
and inexpert police work.

34:19.683 --> 34:21.268
Aren't you forgetting a step?

34:21.727 --> 34:23.144
Before you walk free,

34:23.145 --> 34:25.313
you gotta stand
in front of a judge and say,

34:25.314 --> 34:26.398
"I'm not guilty.

34:28.067 --> 34:30.444
"I'm not the Unabomber.
I didn't write the manifesto,

34:30.778 --> 34:33.488
"didn't elude the FBI
for two decades.

34:33.489 --> 34:36.784
I'm just a nobody
who stands for nothing."

34:36.950 --> 34:39.202
No.

34:39.203 --> 34:42.955
See, your--your logic is flawed.

34:42.956 --> 34:45.124
I'm gonna be acquitted
on a technicality,

34:45.125 --> 34:46.585
not on the merits of the case.

34:47.211 --> 34:50.922
I won't be saying
that I'm not the Unabomber.

34:50.923 --> 34:54.342
You say that on TV,
then people who admire you, like me,

34:54.343 --> 34:55.761
are just gonna think
you're a hypocrite.

34:56.637 --> 34:59.055
You're just betraying your own principles
to save your own skin.

34:59.056 --> 35:00.224
No, you gotta stand up.

35:00.891 --> 35:02.934
You got to take ownership
of what you wrote.

35:02.935 --> 35:05.228
Otherwise, your legacy,
the manifesto will vanish.

35:05.229 --> 35:06.771
The manifesto will not vanish

35:06.772 --> 35:08.815
because the manifesto
has been published,

35:08.816 --> 35:11.819
and more importantly,
the manifesto happens to be right.

35:12.236 --> 35:13.653
Doesn't matter if it's right.

35:13.654 --> 35:14.904
People don't believe in you,

35:14.905 --> 35:16.365
they won't believe in the manifesto.

35:16.907 --> 35:19.952
Are you, one man, doing it all alone,

35:20.828 --> 35:22.745
or are you a leader of men,

35:22.746 --> 35:25.039
a man who can change the world,

35:25.040 --> 35:27.835
who can make a difference
and can leave a legacy behind?

35:28.335 --> 35:29.837
Because you can't be both.

35:32.089 --> 35:34.007
Can't eat your cake
and have it, too, Ted.

35:37.427 --> 35:38.595
What about you, Fitz?

35:39.972 --> 35:41.598
What's your legacy?

35:42.516 --> 35:43.851
What are you leaving behind?

35:45.978 --> 35:49.857
My family, my sons,
they're my legacy.

35:50.023 --> 35:52.191
So they were out
in the woods with you?

35:52.192 --> 35:54.443
- Mm-mm. No. They weren't.
- No. They weren't.

35:54.444 --> 35:55.903
So why do you think you said that?

35:55.904 --> 35:57.613
Why do you think you're lying to me?

35:57.614 --> 35:58.781
I wasn't lying.
It's complicated.

35:58.782 --> 36:00.908
It's not complicated.
It's simple.

36:00.909 --> 36:02.744
They're not your legacy. I am.

36:04.454 --> 36:05.663
You're not my legacy.

36:05.664 --> 36:07.290
You're here because catching me

36:07.291 --> 36:09.542
is the only meaningful thing
you've ever accomplished.

36:09.543 --> 36:11.794
And now I'm gonna walk,
you can feel it slipping away.

36:11.795 --> 36:13.213
If you walk,
you will lose all respect.

36:15.007 --> 36:16.800
Are you talking about me or you?

36:19.178 --> 36:22.597
Because, see, it's you
that spent your whole life

36:22.598 --> 36:24.640
desperate for respect,
desperate to prove

36:24.641 --> 36:26.225
that you're smarter
than the people around you,

36:26.226 --> 36:27.810
and for a brief moment,
you were.

36:27.811 --> 36:29.271
You were the guy
that caught the Unabomber.

36:30.355 --> 36:33.149
But I'm about to walk,
and the whole world will see

36:33.150 --> 36:35.693
that you are just
a knuckle-dragging beat cop,

36:35.694 --> 36:37.696
and the graffiti squad
was where you belonged.

36:38.280 --> 36:42.242
You know, the thing I find
most sad about you, James,

36:42.409 --> 36:45.161
is that you can run off
and live in the woods,

36:45.162 --> 36:46.996
abandoning your wife and kids,

36:46.997 --> 36:49.582
study the manifesto down to the letter,

36:49.583 --> 36:52.753
but it will not make one jot
of difference to anyone,

36:54.004 --> 36:55.964
and the best that you will ever be

36:57.633 --> 36:59.843
is a feeble imitation of me.

37:45.347 --> 37:47.266
I've got some concerns
about Leo Burt.

37:47.474 --> 37:49.851
He's our best suspect,
but he's also our most elusive.

37:52.104 --> 37:54.314
Uh, Fitz, uh, you weren't
on the list for this meeting,

37:54.648 --> 37:57.191
so if we need you,
we will give you a buzz.

37:57.192 --> 38:00.152
This is a new profile.
It's clean, no typos, solid.

38:00.153 --> 38:01.488
Goodbye, Fitz.

38:04.283 --> 38:05.242
Just trying to help.

38:06.285 --> 38:07.911
This is based on what exactly?

38:08.120 --> 38:10.329
Forensics.
It's grounded in forensics.

38:10.330 --> 38:12.040
- Forensics?
- I've come up with an approach

38:12.332 --> 38:14.166
I'm calling forensic linguistics.

38:14.167 --> 38:15.751
Fingerprints are forensics.

38:15.752 --> 38:17.753
DNA is forensics.

38:17.754 --> 38:20.256
Spelling "wilfully" with one L
is not forensics.

38:20.257 --> 38:22.758
It's not just spelling.
It's a comprehensive idiolectic profile--

38:22.759 --> 38:25.679
Fitz, we don't want a profile.
We want a person.

38:26.847 --> 38:28.682
Can you get us a person
that we can put on the board?

38:29.391 --> 38:31.476
- I think if you just read it...
- I didn't think so.

38:32.019 --> 38:34.813
Give me a name
that I can put on the board.

38:35.772 --> 38:38.150
Otherwise, shut the door behind you.

38:48.618 --> 38:49.703
Toss that thing.

38:55.083 --> 38:56.709
Okay. Where were we?

38:56.710 --> 38:59.171
We've got the top five,
counting Leo Burt.

39:12.601 --> 39:14.144
Fitz, thinking:
<i>Look at this obedient sheep.</i>

39:14.519 --> 39:16.772
<i>Gotta make them hear you.
Gotta make them listen.</i>

39:37.709 --> 39:40.921
You're gonna make them listen.
You're gonna make them hear you.

39:45.884 --> 39:46.843
How?

39:47.928 --> 39:49.303
How?

39:52.641 --> 39:54.309
- Who's my liaison?
- Over here.

39:57.938 --> 39:59.271
Tell the lab to drop
everything else.

39:59.272 --> 40:00.648
This is all hands on deck.

40:00.649 --> 40:01.900
Copy that. We're on it.

40:02.192 --> 40:03.734
Get the originals down to forensics.

40:03.735 --> 40:04.985
Follow me.

40:17.707 --> 40:19.918
They're from him.
They're all from him.

40:38.270 --> 40:39.896
Jesus, I'm gonna go get him.

40:50.991 --> 40:53.784
Why didn't you answer my pages?
You gotta come in.

40:53.785 --> 40:56.037
We just got a bunch of
new Unabom letters.

40:56.580 --> 40:59.249
He's written to <i>The Times,
The Washington Post, Penthouse.</i>

41:00.709 --> 41:01.877
You're not gonna believe this.

41:02.752 --> 41:04.337
The Unabomber wants to make a deal.

41:21.396 --> 41:24.566
Well, what the hell do we do now?
